- Trial expiry UX requirement is not met. `TrialExpiredDialog` only has a single “Close” button; required behavior is a friendly expiry screen with “Get Full License” + “Quit” actions.
- Runtime expiry path is not trial-specific. In `start_license_watchdog`, fatal expiry still shows `LockScreen` and deletes license files, rather than showing the new trial-expired dialog for trial builds.
- Roblox bundle download token is not single-use. `/api/roblox_bundle/download/<token>` validates TTL but never consumes/removes token on successful download, violating the explicit single-use token requirement.
- Admin dashboard requirement to expose a copyable public trial download link on the trial config row is not implemented (no `download_trial` link in `builds.html`).

Additional notable gap:
- Build config form uses “Trial duration (seconds)” instead of requested hours UX. Backend supports seconds field, but admin-facing requirement was hours.

Security:
- Serious concern: non-single-use bundle tokens increase replay/download abuse window.
- Positive: separate trial HMAC secret path is implemented; trial register endpoint includes rate limiting.

Next actions (high impact):
1) Fix launcher trial gating: only auto-register when `IS_TRIAL` and no saved key; on expired trial key, show TrialExpiredDialog (no re-mint path).
2) Implement required trial-expired UX (Get Full License + Quit), and route watchdog fatal expiry for trial builds to that dialog.
